  "usageNotes": {
    "teacherGuidance": "Use grid paper for drawing bar graphs in class. Start with a scale of 1, then progress to scales of 2 and 5. Let students collect their own data to graph.",
    "parentGuidance": "Help your child draw bar graphs at home using squared paper. They can graph things like the number of each type of toy, or how many pages they read each day.",
    "studentGuidance": "A bar graph uses bars to show data. Taller bars mean bigger numbers! Always read the scale on the side to know what each line means."
